{"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokensraw"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"OUDSTokensRaw"}],"symbolKind":"module","title":"OUDSTokensRaw","role":"collection","roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"OUDSTokensRaw"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In fact, we choose to use as most as possible primitive types for raw values, like ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"CGFloat","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" so as to handle the smallest types with few impacts on the memory for ecodesign principles. Indeed with hundreds of raw tokens, it will be more efficient to store primitive small types than Swift "},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" objects."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"So we expose also in higher level some properties so as to convert when needed some of these types to ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" types (like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Font.Weight"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Color"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To keep the same semantics as the ones used in our specifications, "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"typealias","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are used to as to make the links to "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"primitive types"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and our logic of "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":". These type aliases are available for those who want to make their own theme."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using more simple and primitive types will help also to test the library. With also type aliases we force users to use our types and not higher level types like ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI"}]},{"type":"text","text":" types."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We also choose to add in ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"extension"}]},{"type":"text","text":" all the tokens values in a separated file so as to help the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"type":"text","text":"-JSON-to-Swift parser to build files to copy and paste easily in the project and keeping all the other objects."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example for "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ColorRawTokens","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Define types for color raw tokens","public typealias ColorRawToken = String","","public enum ColorRawTokens { } \/\/ Gathers all color raw tokens","","extension ColorRawTokens { \/\/ In a separated file","","    public static let colorFunctionalWhite: ColorRawToken = \"#FFFFFF\"","    public static let colorFunctionalScarlet400: ColorRawToken = \"#FF4D4E\"","    public static let colorTransparentBlack0: ColorRawToken = apply(opacity: OpacityRawTokens.opacity0, on: colorFunctionalBlack)","    ...","}","","extension String {","    public var color: Color { \/\/ Helper for SwiftUI","        Color(hexadecimalCode: self)","    }","}"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Architecture","text":"Architecture","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Composites","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" folder contains some ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composite class"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" defined to match the objects available in ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In fact the design system implementations should expose pack of values so as to gather several tokens in one object. For exemple ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ElevationCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used for predefined elevations effects, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TypographyCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used for predefined typography."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"All such ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composites"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are defined here."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Declarations","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" folder contains all the Swift "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enum"},{"text":" objects which will gather the raw tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"In fact, raw tokens are defined as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"static let"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"stored properties"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", an adding them in an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enum"},{"type":"text","text":" is more optimized for namespaces reasons. Thus all "},{"code":"public enum","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" gathering raw tokens are defined there.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TypeAliases"}]},{"text":" folder contains all the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"typealias"}]},{"text":" values used for the raw tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Indeed these aliases are here to bring clarity and meanings in the library, and also to help users (i.e. developers) to know what kind of objects they handle with the same vocabulary as the one used in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"text":", and in general, in the whole design system. They can be seen as a ligh level of abstraction with meanings, without having to define real types with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Values","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" folder is maybe the hotter one.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In fact all the raw tokens values are defined there, and if a JSON to Swift parser generate files, these files must be stored there. It contains only pure raw tokens Swift values, without any type aliases definitions or objects declarations. Generated values are place din "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+Values"}]},{"type":"text","text":" files, and composite raw tokens are in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+Composites"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a nutshell, place the generated values somewhere, and the types and objects elsewhere."}]},{"text":"Raw tokens management","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Raw-tokens-management"},{"type":"heading","text":"How to add raw tokens","anchor":"How-to-add-raw-tokens","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, you need to define which from family this semantic comes. We have today up to 7 families: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"border"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"color","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"dimension"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"elevation","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"grid","type":"text"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"opacity","type":"text"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"typography"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If your token is not from one of these groups, maybe you should redesign your token or create a new family. To do that, you will have to create a dedicated Swift ","type":"text"},{"code":"enum","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", with a useful name, and declare as a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"static let"},{"type":"text","text":" the raw tokens in an "},{"code":"extension","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If you already know the family, just update the matching files.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to define Swift "},{"code":"typealias","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", update the suitable file in the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"TypeAliases","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" folder."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Please, respect the nomenclature of the files, e.g. for a new family “Awesome raw” tokens:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declaration of raw tokens family must be "},{"code":"AwesomeRawTokens.swift","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"generated values must be in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AwesomeRawTokens+Values.swift"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"composite tokens must be in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AwesomeRawTokens+Composites.swift"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"type aliases must be in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AwesomeRawTokens+Aliases.swift"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"composites objects must be in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AwesomeCompositeRawTokens.swift"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Composites"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" here are notions from the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figjam"}]},{"text":", a bit, but ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is not able to manage such gorup of raw tokens. This it cannot output composite raw tokens in the JSON for the parser."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"As a consequence the composites are defined in a folder, and their values in the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Values","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" folder in dedicated files."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It may imply some synchornization issues between the raw tokens and the composite tokens using them, but we don’t have any solution yet.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, update the unit tests. We do not test the raw tokens values as they are, because these values will be generated and keeping up to date the unit tests may be time wasting.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"But we can however test the relationships between tokens, for exemple for colors if they go lighter and lighter, or for dimensions if they go smaller and smaller. If some raw tokens like font weights strongly rely on the values, we still test these values.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How to update or remove raw tokens","anchor":"How-to-update-or-remove-raw-tokens","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Quite simple, find the raw token you want to update or remove, and update or remove it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"But beware, if you change the name of the property or if you move it from an "},{"code":"enum","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to another, or if you remove the token, you must keep retrocompatibility as much as possible so as to avoid to break any public API. Keep also the CHANGELOG and\/or the release updated with some BREAKING CHANGE notification, and also the Git history clean."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you update the value, keep also the CHANGELOG and\/or RELEASE NOTE updated so as to let yout users know the variables have been changed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Raw tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" are smallest "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"tokens"}]},{"text":" possible. They are associated to raw values and will be finaly the values assigned to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"components","type":"text"}]},{"text":" properties.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/BorderRawTokens","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ColorRawTokens","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/DimensionRawTokens","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ElevationRawTokens","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/GridRawTokens","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/OpacityRawTokens","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyRawTokens"],"title":"Group"},{"title":"Classes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ElevationCompositeRawToken"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyCompositeRawToken"],"title":"Structures"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/BorderRadiusRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/BorderStyleRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/BorderWidthRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ColorRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/DimensionRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ElevationRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/GridRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/OpacityRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontFamilyRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontLetterSpacingRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontLineHeightRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontSizeRawToken","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontWeightRawToken"],"title":"Type Aliases"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/ColorRawTokens":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ColorRawTokens","abstract":[{"text":"Defined as the group of all ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"raw tokens"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" related to ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"colors","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Primitive types such as  ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" must be used to as to allow to use "},{"code":"@objc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keywords in extensions for overriding.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Such tokens are packed in a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift enum","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" so as to gather them in one object with the suitable namespace and avoid to have just constants in nothing else"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(i.e. publicly accessible from everywhere). More optimized than ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"struct"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic","title":"ColorRawTokens","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/colorrawtokens","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ColorRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ColorRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/OpacityRawToken":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Raw tokens of opacity are finaly ","type":"text"},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OpacityRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/OpacityRawToken","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OpacityRawToken"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/opacityrawtoken","role":"symbol","title":"OpacityRawToken"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/ElevationCompositeRawToken":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"In the global design system, composite tokens are defined for elevation effects.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It is defined as a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"final class"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"NSObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" so as to be shared through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@objc"},{"text":" with extensions and protocols within modules.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/elevationcompositerawtoken","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ElevationCompositeRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"ElevationCompositeRawToken","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ElevationCompositeRawToken"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ElevationCompositeRawToken"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/TypographyFontWeightRawToken":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In the global design system tool, "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"font weight"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" raw tokens are basically ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values, to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontWeightRawToken","role":"symbol","title":"TypographyFontWeightRawToken","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypographyFontWeightRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypographyFontWeightRawToken"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/typographyfontweightrawtoken"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/ElevationRawTokens":{"title":"ElevationRawTokens","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/elevationrawtokens","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ElevationRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ElevationRawTokens","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ElevationRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Defined as the group of all "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens","type":"text"}]},{"text":" related to ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"elevations"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Primitive types such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGFloat"},{"text":" must be used to as to allow to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"@objc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keywords in extensions for overriding.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Such tokens are packed in a "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift enum"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" so as to gather them in one object with the suitable namespace and avoid to have just constants in nothing else","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(i.e. publicly accessible from everywhere). More optimized than "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"struct","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/TypographyFontFamilyRawToken":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TypographyFontFamilyRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypographyFontFamilyRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"In the global design system tool, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"font family","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" raw tokens are basically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" values, to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar."}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/typographyfontfamilyrawtoken","title":"TypographyFontFamilyRawToken","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontFamilyRawToken","kind":"symbol"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/TypographyFontLetterSpacingRawToken":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontLetterSpacingRawToken","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypographyFontLetterSpacingRawToken"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypographyFontLetterSpacingRawToken"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/typographyfontletterspacingrawtoken","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In the global design system tool, "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"font letter spacing"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" raw tokens are basically "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGFloat"},{"type":"text","text":" values, to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"TypographyFontLetterSpacingRawToken","role":"symbol"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/TypographyCompositeRawToken":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyCompositeRawToken","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypographyCompositeRawToken"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypographyCompositeRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/typographycompositerawtoken","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Composite raw tokens are here to pack a set of specific values according to the global design system tool."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Here a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"typography","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is finaly defined by some specific values."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"TypographyCompositeRawToken","role":"symbol"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/TypographyFontLineHeightRawToken":{"abstract":[{"text":"In the global design system tool, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"font line height","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" raw tokens are basically "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGFloat"},{"text":" values, to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/TypographyFontLineHeightRawToken","title":"TypographyFontLineHeightRawToken","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/typographyfontlineheightrawtoken","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypographyFontLineHeightRawToken"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypographyFontLineHeightRawToken","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/ElevationRawToken":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/ElevationRawToken","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/elevationrawtoken","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ElevationRawToken"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Type aliases precising ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGFloat"},{"text":" values are used (because used in ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI"}]},{"text":" API) for each ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"elevation raw token","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ElevationRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ElevationRawToken","type":"topic"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/DimensionRawToken":{"title":"DimensionRawToken","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/dimensionrawtoken","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DimensionRawToken"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/DimensionRawToken","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DimensionRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Raw tokens of dimensions are finaly "},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar."}]},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/GridRawToken":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GridRawToken"}],"fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GridRawToken"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/gridrawtoken","abstract":[{"text":"In the global design system tool, the notion of “raw tokens of grids” exist but refers always to dimension raw tokens,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to keep grammar clean and clear with design system grammar.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GridRawToken","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/GridRawToken"},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/DimensionRawTokens":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/DimensionRawTokens","abstract":[{"text":"Defined as the group of all ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" related to "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dimensions","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Primitive types such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Double"},{"type":"text","text":" must be used to as to allow to use "},{"code":"@objc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keywords in extensions for overriding.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Such tokens are packed in a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift enum","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" so as to gather them in one object with the suitable namespace and avoid to have just constants in nothing else"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(i.e. publicly accessible from everywhere). More optimized than ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"struct"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"DimensionRawTokens","url":"\/documentation\/oudstokensraw\/dimensionrawtokens","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DimensionRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DimensionRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OUDSTokensRaw/documentation/OUDSTokensRaw/OpacityRawTokens":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OpacityRawTokens"}],"title":"OpacityRawTokens","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OpacityRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Defined as the group of all "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"raw tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" related to "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"opacity","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Primitive types such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Double"},{"type":"text","text":" must be used to as to allow to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@objc"},{"type":"text","text":" keywords in extensions for overriding."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Such tokens are packed in a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift enum","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" so as to gather them in one object with the suitable namespace and avoid to have just constants in nothing else"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(i.e. publicly accessible from everywhere). More optimized than ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"struct","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensRaw\/documentation\/OUDSTokensRaw\/OpacityRawTokens